  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel the skin of the pineapple and chop it up into small bite-sized chunks, you will need roughly 400g for this recipe. Enjoy the rest as a snack while you cook."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Blend up half the pineapple with half an onion and three cloves of garlic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour this over the chicken and allow it to marinate in the fridge for 30 mins. The pineapple helps to tenderise the chicken."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely dice your remaining onion and the tomatoes. Grate the remaining two cloves of garlic and ginger."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a large wok, add in 50ml of vegetable oil and fry the onions on a medium heat for 5 mins until lightly browned. Add in the grated garlic and ginger and fry for 2 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, you’re going to want to add in the chilli powder, turmeric, garam masala, ground cumin and 2 tsp salt. Fry for 30 seconds until fragrant."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip in the chopped tomato (along with their juices) and cook for 5 mins until the sauce is thick and jammy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your marinated chicken to the pot and coconut milk, then give it a good mix. Put a lid on and allow it to simmer for 20 mins, stirring regularly. The pineapple has a lot of sugar so it has a tendency to burn. Keep an eye out for that."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Halfway through the 20 mins, add in the remaining chopped pineapple."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, finely chop the coriander."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the chicken is fully cooked, add in the coriander, the juice of two limes and 1 tbsp freshly ground black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Season to taste and serve with freshly steamed rice."
    }
  ],
